I added the `inject_user` decorator. All it does is call `retrieve_user` behind the scenes and stick the result of that into the keyword args for your endpoint.

```python
@sanic_app.route("/protected/user")
    @sanic_jwt.inject_user()
    @sanic_jwt.protected()
    async def my_protected_user(request, user):
        return json({
            'user_id': user.user_id
        })
```

